<h4>Money for training for personal health budget holders &ndash; open now</h4>
<p>If you support people who use a personal health budget to employ their own personal assistant, they can apply for money for training from Skills for Care.&nbsp;This can be used to pay for training for themselves as employers, or to develop the skills of their PAs. This can be used to pay for training for themselves as employers, or to develop the skills of their PAs. It can cover any related costs, including backfill and travel expenses.&nbsp;Every application is reviewed on a case by case basis and there are lots of courses they could apply for.&nbsp;Download an application form from the&nbsp;<a target="_blank" class="sys_16" href="http://www.skillsforcare.org.uk/Learning-development/Funding/Individual-employer-funding/Personal-Health-Budget-PHB-holders.aspx?utm_source=NHS-England&amp;amp%3Butm_medium=Email&amp;amp%3Butm_campaign=PHBfunding">Skills for Care website</a>&nbsp;or email: <a target="_blank" class="sys_16" href="mailto:funding@skillsforcare.org.uk">funding@skillsforcare.org.uk</a></p>
<p>Help Skills for Care promote the funding, click&nbsp;here to&nbsp;<a target="_blank" class="sys_16" href="mailto:marketing@skillsforcare.org.uk">request printed copies</a>.</p>
